-- Cemex Falls to the Lowest Price Since August on Planned Ready Mix USA Deal
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2010-10-11T17:32:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/cemex-falls-to-the-lowest-price-since-august-on-planned-ready-mix-usa-deal.html
Cemex SAB , the largest cement maker
in the Americas, dropped to the lowest price since August after
announcing plans to acquire the interests of partner Ready Mix
USA LLC in two joint ventures for about $360 million.  Cemex dropped 2.6 percent to 10.15 pesos at 1:23 p.m. New
York time, The shares fell as much as 4 percent to 10 pesos, the
lowest price on an intraday basis since Aug. 25.  The transaction, which is part of a put option by Ready Mix
USA, is expected to close in September 2011, Monterrey, Mexico-
based Cemex said in an e-mailed statement on Oct. 8. Cemex will
take on about $17 million of debt from one of the ventures,
which were created in 2005.  “This news complicates the outlook for next year,” said
 Ramon Ortiz , an analyst at Corp. Actinver SA. “If the recovery
doesn’t come as hoped, this would be adding pressure above all
in the coming year.”  The joint venture operated by Cemex owns a cement plant in
Alabama with annual capacity of 900,000 tons, a cement plant in
Georgia with 800,000 tons of capacity and 12 cement terminals,
the company said. The joint venture operated by Ready Mix USA
owns 10 sand and gravel pits, 149 concrete plants and 20
concrete block makers in Arkansas, Mississippi, Tennessee,
Alabama, Georgia and Florida.  Mexico benchmark IPC  index  climbed 0.4 percent to
34,599.31.  To contact the reporter on this story:
